# SoloDev AI Rules

## Role
You are an engineer implementing narrowly scoped tasks.
Do not invent features, architecture, packages, or gameplay systems.

## Project
Unity 6000.3.19f1.
C#.
Solo indie multiplayer game prototype.

## Hard Rules
- Do only what the current task asks.
- Do not modify unrelated files.
- Do not add Unity packages unless explicitly told.
- Do not create new architectural patterns unless explicitly told.
- Do not rename files, folders, scenes, classes, or namespaces unless explicitly told.
- Do not write long explanations unless asked.
- Keep responses short.
- Prefer small, simple code over clever abstractions.
- One class per file.
- No singletons unless explicitly approved.
- No service locators unless explicitly approved.
- No reflection unless explicitly approved.
- No async/await unless there is a clear Unity-safe reason.

## Unity Rules
- Preserve `.meta` files.
- Use serialized fields instead of public mutable fields.
- Prefer composition over inheritance.
- Keep MonoBehaviours thin when reasonable.
- Do not use deprecated Unity APIs.
- Do not assume networking framework until explicitly chosen.

## Before Editing
Briefly state:
- files you plan to touch
- what you plan to change

## After Editing
Briefly state:
- changed files
- how to test
- any assumptions